categorydescription:
Technovent USA Home Page...
Manufacturers of:
• MagnaCap® implant retained magnetic attachment system
• Specialized silicone materials for maxillofacial prosthesis
• Prosthetic adhesives
Technovent USA through Factor II, Inc. provides specially formulated silicone materials, the MagnaCap® system of prosthesis magnets and implant abutments & caps to the US market. We work closely with clinical technicians to ensure our materials always meet the specific working processes of busy maxillofacial prosthetics units. Our products are manufactured to the highest quality standards and are 510K registered as medical devices under the appropriate FDA regulations.
Need help? Check out our Magnet Order Guide and our Vistafix Guide
Need help? Check out our Magnet Order Guide and our Vistafix Guide

S-Range System
The technology and functional durability of Technovent products has been established over many years of research, development and clinical use. The system meets the material requirements for use with commercially pure titanium implant systems and has enhanced surface wear-resistance to provide practical functional life for dental applications. In intra-oral, extra-oral and craniofacial use, the magnets will outlast the normal aesthetic life of most craniofacial body prostheses and dentures.
INTRODUCING: The S-Range System
The new S-Range system is the culmination of over 10 years of research and development. The unique design of the prosthesis magnets when used in conjunction with the new S-Range Magnacaps/ Magnabutments gives approximately 80% increase in magnetic retention. The system includes two new, low-profile, high strength magnets.
CLICK HERE to view the TechnoventUSA website for phone orders.

IMPLANT ATTACHMENTS
Our range of implant attachment options includes abutments to fit directly into the implant and also caps to fit an already present abutment.
Our caps and abutments are produced to fit the most popularly used implant systems though we can produce custom/special fittings for individual patient situations and other implants as requested.
